-0 right-0 p-5",children:[y.jsxs("p",{className:"text-white text-sm font-medium leading-snug italic mb-2",children:['"',e.quote,'"']}),y.jsx("p",{className:"text-teal-300 text-xs font-semibold",children:e.name})]})]},t))})]})})]})}const dm=[{id:"anxiety",title:"Anxiety Screening",shortTitle:"Anxiety",description:"Assess your anxiety levels with this validated-style questionnaire based on generalized anxiety symptoms.",icon:"Brain",color:"from-teal-500 to-cyan-500",bgColor:"bg-teal-50",textColor:"text-teal-700",questions:["I feel nervous, anxious, or on edge","I am not able to stop or control worrying","I worry too much about different things","I have trouble relaxing","I am so restless that it is hard to sit still","I become easily annoyed or irritable","I feel afraid, as if something awful might happen","I have difficulty concentrating because of worry","My muscles feel tense due to anxiety","I have trouble falling asleep due to anxious thoughts"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Minimal",color:"text-green-600",advice:"Your anxiety levels appear to be within a normal range. Continue practicing healthy habits like regular exercise, good sleep hygiene, and mindfulness."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Mild",color:"text-yellow-600",advice:"You may be experiencing mild anxiety. Consider incorporating relaxation techniques, deep breathing exercises, and regular physical activity into your routine."},{min:20,max:29,level:"Moderate",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"Your responses suggest moderate anxiety levels. It would be beneficial to speak with a mental health professional who can provide personalized strategies and support."},{min:30,max:40,level:"Severe",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your responses indicate significant anxiety symptoms. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional as soon as possible. You deserve support and there are effective treatments available."}]},{id:"depression",title:"Depression Screening",shortTitle:"Depression",description:"Evaluate symptoms of depression using this structured questionnaire based on common depressive indicators.",icon:"CloudRain",color:"from-blue-500 to-indigo-500",bgColor:"bg-blue-50",textColor:"text-blue-700",questions:["I have little interest or pleasure in doing things","I feel down, depressed, or hopeless","I have trouble falling or staying asleep, or sleeping too much","I feel tired or have little energy","I have poor appetite or am overeating","I feel bad about myself — or feel like a failure","I have trouble concentrating on things","I move or speak slowly, or am fidgety and restless","I have thoughts that I would be better off dead","I feel disconnected from people around me"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Minimal",color:"text-green-600",advice:"Your depression indicators appear minimal. Maintain your well-being through social connections, physical activity, and activities you enjoy."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Mild",color:"text-yellow-600",advice:"You may be experiencing mild depressive symptoms. Try to stay connected with loved ones, engage in activities that bring joy, and maintain a regular routine."},{min:20,max:29,level:"Moderate",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"Your responses suggest moderate depression. Speaking with a counselor or therapist could be very helpful. You don't have to face this alone."},{min:30,max:40,level:"Severe",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your responses indicate significant depressive symptoms. Please reach out to a mental health professional or contact one of the support resources listed on our platform. Help is available and recovery is possible."}]},{id:"smartphone-addiction",title:"Smartphone Addiction Scale",shortTitle:"Phone Addiction",description:"Measure your level of smartphone dependency and its impact on your daily life.",icon:"Smartphone",color:"from-purple-500 to-pink-500",bgColor:"bg-purple-50",textColor:"text-purple-700",questions:["I feel anxious when my phone is not nearby","I check my phone first thing in the morning","I spend more time on my phone than I intend to","I feel the urge to use my phone during conversations","I have tried to reduce phone use but failed","I lose track of time while using my phone","I use my phone to avoid dealing with problems","My phone use interferes with my sleep","I feel restless if I cannot use my phone","My relationships suffer due to my phone use"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Low Risk",color:"text-green-600",advice:"You appear to have a healthy relationship with your smartphone. Keep maintaining boundaries around screen time."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Mild Risk",color:"text-yellow-600",advice:"You show some signs of phone dependency. Try setting screen time limits and creating phone-free zones in your daily routine."},{min:20,max:29,level:"Moderate Risk",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"Your smartphone use may be affecting your well-being. Consider a digital detox plan and explore alternative activities for relaxation."},{min:30,max:40,level:"High Risk",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your phone use patterns suggest significant dependency. Consider speaking with a counselor about developing healthier digital habits."}]},{id:"pornography-addiction",title:"Pornography Use Assessment",shortTitle:"Pornography",description:"Assess whether your pornography consumption patterns may be affecting your well-being.",icon:"ShieldAlert",color:"from-rose-500 to-red-500",bgColor:"bg-rose-50",textColor:"text-rose-700",questions:["I spend more time viewing pornography than intended","I have tried to stop or reduce but couldn't","I feel guilty or ashamed after viewing","My pornography use affects my relationships","I use pornography to cope with stress or emotions","I need increasingly extreme content to feel satisfied","I neglect responsibilities due to pornography use","I feel anxious when I cannot access pornography","My self-image has been affected by pornography","I hide my pornography use from others"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Low Concern",color:"text-green-600",advice:"Your responses suggest low concern in this area. Maintaining awareness of your habits is always beneficial."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Mild Concern",color:"text-yellow-600",advice:"Some patterns may warrant attention. Consider reflecting on your habits and how they align with your values and goals."},{min:20,max:29,level:"Moderate Concern",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"Your responses suggest this may be impacting your well-being. Speaking with a counselor in a confidential setting could provide valuable support."},{min:30,max:40,level:"Significant Concern",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your responses indicate this is significantly affecting your life. Professional support can help you develop healthier patterns. Please reach out to a therapist or counselor."}]},{id:"self-harm",title:"Self-Harm & Self-Loathing Assessment",shortTitle:"Self-Harm",description:"A supportive screening for self-harm thoughts and self-critical patterns.",icon:"HeartCrack",color:"from-red-500 to-orange-500",bgColor:"bg-red-50",textColor:"text-red-700",questions:["I have thoughts of hurting myself","I feel I am worthless or a burden to others","I engage in behaviors that I know are harmful to me","I punish myself when things go wrong","I feel intense self-hatred or self-criticism","I have difficulty caring about my own well-being","I isolate myself when feeling distressed","I feel numb and want to feel something, anything","I believe I deserve to suffer","I have acted on urges to hurt myself"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Low Risk",color:"text-green-600",advice:"Your responses indicate low risk. Continue nurturing self-compassion and reaching out when you need support."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Mild Risk",color:"text-yellow-600",advice:"You may be experiencing some self-critical thoughts. Practice self-compassion exercises and consider talking to someone you trust."},{min:20,max:29,level:"Moderate Risk",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"Your responses suggest you may be struggling. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional. You are worthy of care and support."},{min:30,max:40,level:"High Risk",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your responses indicate you may be in distress. Please reach out to a crisis helpline or mental health professional immediately. You matter, and help is available right now."}]},{id:"quality-of-life",title:"Quality of Life Assessment",shortTitle:"Quality of Life",description:"Evaluate your overall life satisfaction and well-being across key domains.",icon:"Sparkles",color:"from-emerald-500 to-teal-500",bgColor:"bg-emerald-50",textColor:"text-emerald-700",questions:["I am satisfied with my physical health","I feel emotionally balanced most days","I have meaningful relationships in my life","I am satisfied with my work or daily activities","I feel a sense of purpose and meaning","I can manage stress effectively","I get enough restful sleep","I engage in activities that bring me joy","I feel safe and secure in my environment","I am optimistic about my future"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Needs Attention",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your quality of life scores suggest several areas need attention. Consider speaking with a professional who can help you develop a plan to improve your well-being."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Below Average",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"There is room for improvement in your quality of life. Focus on small, achievable changes in areas that matter most to you."},{min:20,max:29,level:"Good",color:"text-yellow-600",advice:"You have a reasonably good quality of life. Continue building on your strengths and addressing areas where you'd like to see improvement."},{min:30,max:40,level:"Excellent",color:"text-green-600",advice:"Your quality of life appears excellent! Continue maintaining the habits and relationships that contribute to your well-being."}]},{id:"alcohol",title:"Alcohol Use Assessment",shortTitle:"Alcohol",description:"Screen for problematic alcohol use patterns and their impact on your life.",icon:"Wine",color:"from-amber-500 to-orange-500",bgColor:"bg-amber-50",textColor:"text-amber-700",questions:["I drink more than I intend to","I have tried to cut down but couldn't","I spend a lot of time drinking or recovering from it","I crave alcohol when I'm not drinking","My drinking interferes with responsibilities","I continue drinking despite relationship problems","I have given up activities I enjoyed because of drinking","I drink in situations where it is physically dangerous","I need more alcohol to get the same effect","I experience withdrawal symptoms when I stop drinking"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Low Risk",color:"text-green-600",advice:"Your alcohol use appears to be within low-risk levels. Continue being mindful of your consumption patterns."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Moderate Risk",color:"text-yellow-600",advice:"You may be developing problematic drinking patterns. Consider setting limits and having alcohol-free days each week."},{min:20,max:29,level:"High Risk",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"Your drinking patterns suggest significant risk. Speaking with a healthcare provider or counselor about your alcohol use would be beneficial."},{min:30,max:40,level:"Severe Risk",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your responses indicate severe alcohol-related concerns. Please seek professional help. Alcohol dependency is treatable, and support is available."}]},{id:"suicide-risk",title:"Suicide Risk Screening",shortTitle:"Suicide Risk",description:"A confidential screening to help identify thoughts or feelings that may indicate suicide risk.",icon:"AlertTriangle",color:"from-red-600 to-rose-600",bgColor:"bg-red-50",textColor:"text-red-700",questions:["I feel that life is not worth living","I wish I could go to sleep and not wake up","I have thoughts about ending my life","I feel like a burden to the people around me","I feel trapped, with no way out of my situation","I experience unbearable emotional pain","I have thought about a specific plan to end my life","I feel hopeless about the future","I have access to means to harm myself","I have previously attempted to end my life"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Low Risk",color:"text-green-600",advice:"Your responses suggest low immediate risk. If you ever feel distressed, don't hesitate to reach out to someone you trust or a helpline."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Moderate Risk",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"Your responses suggest some concerning thoughts. Please talk to someone you trust — a friend, family member, or counselor. You don't have to face this alone."},{min:20,max:29,level:"High Risk",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your responses indicate significant distress. Please reach out to a crisis helpline or go to your nearest emergency room. Your life has value and help is available right now."},{min:30,max:40,level:"Crisis Level",color:"text-red-700",advice:"⚠️ URGENT: Please contact emergency services or a crisis helpline immediately. Call Uganda Crisis Line or go to the nearest hospital. You are not alone, and immediate help is available."}]},{id:"stress",title:"Stress Level Assessment",shortTitle:"Stress",description:"Measure your current stress levels and understand how stress may be affecting your well-being.",icon:"Flame",color:"from-orange-500 to-yellow-500",bgColor:"bg-orange-50",textColor:"text-orange-700",questions:["I feel overwhelmed by my responsibilities","I have difficulty relaxing even when I have time","I feel irritable or angry more than usual","I experience physical symptoms from stress (headaches, tension)","I have trouble sleeping due to worries","I feel unable to cope with the demands placed on me","I lack time for activities I enjoy","I feel emotionally drained at the end of the day","I have difficulty making decisions","I feel my stress is affecting my health"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Low Stress",color:"text-green-600",advice:"Your stress levels appear manageable. Continue with your current coping strategies and self-care practices."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Moderate Stress",color:"text-yellow-600",advice:"You're experiencing moderate stress. Incorporate stress-reduction techniques like exercise, meditation, or hobby time into your routine."},{min:20,max:29,level:"High Stress",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"Your stress levels are high. Consider making changes to reduce demands, delegating tasks, and speaking with a professional about stress management strategies."},{min:30,max:40,level:"Severe Stress",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your stress levels are severe and may be affecting your health. Please prioritize seeking professional support and making immediate changes to reduce your stress load."}]},{id:"drug-use",title:"Drug Use Assessment",shortTitle:"Drug Use",description:"Screen for potentially harmful drug use patterns and their impact on your daily life.",icon:"Pill",color:"from-violet-500 to-purple-500",bgColor:"bg-violet-50",textColor:"text-violet-700",questions:["I use substances to cope with stress or emotions","I have increased the amount or frequency of drug use","I have tried to stop but couldn't","I experience cravings for drugs","My drug use interferes with daily responsibilities","I continue using despite knowing the negative effects","I have given up activities because of drug use","I use drugs in dangerous situations","I experience withdrawal symptoms when not using","My relationships suffer due to my drug use"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Low Risk",color:"text-green-600",advice:"Your responses suggest low risk from drug use. Continue making informed and healthy choices."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Moderate Risk",color:"text-yellow-600",advice:"Some patterns suggest growing risk. Reflect on your substance use and consider speaking with a healthcare provider."},{min:20,max:29,level:"High Risk",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"Your drug use patterns indicate significant risk. Professional support can help you develop healthier coping mechanisms."},{min:30,max:40,level:"Severe Risk",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your responses indicate severe substance use concerns. Please seek professional help immediately. Recovery is possible with the right support."}]},{id:"nicotine",title:"Nicotine Dependency Assessment",shortTitle:"Nicotine",description:"Evaluate your level of nicotine dependency and its impact on your health.",icon:"Wind",color:"from-slate-500 to-gray-500",bgColor:"bg-slate-50",textColor:"text-slate-700",questions:["I smoke or use nicotine products daily","I feel a strong urge to use nicotine when I haven't recently","I use nicotine within the first hour of waking","I have tried to quit but returned to use","I feel irritable or anxious without nicotine","I use nicotine to manage stress or emotions","I have increased the amount I use over time","I continue using despite knowing health risks","I find it difficult to go without nicotine for a day","My nicotine use affects my physical fitness"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Low Dependency",color:"text-green-600",advice:"Your nicotine dependency appears low. If you use nicotine products, this is a great time to consider quitting."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Mild Dependency",color:"text-yellow-600",advice:"You show signs of mild nicotine dependency. Consider nicotine reduction strategies and speak with a healthcare provider about quitting options."},{min:20,max:29,level:"Moderate Dependency",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"You have moderate nicotine dependency. Professional cessation programs and nicotine replacement therapy could be very helpful."},{min:30,max:40,level:"Severe Dependency",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your nicotine dependency is severe. Please consult a healthcare provider about comprehensive cessation treatment options."}]},{id:"sleep-quality",title:"Sleep Quality Assessment",shortTitle:"Sleep",description:"Assess your sleep quality and identify factors that may be affecting your rest.",icon:"Moon",color:"from-indigo-500 to-blue-500",bgColor:"bg-indigo-50",textColor:"text-indigo-700",questions:["I have difficulty falling asleep at night","I wake up during the night and have trouble getting back to sleep","I feel unrested when I wake up in the morning","I feel sleepy during the day","I rely on substances (caffeine, alcohol, medication) to sleep","My sleep schedule is irregular","I use screens (phone, TV) right before bed","I worry or think excessively when trying to sleep","My sleep quality affects my daily functioning","I feel that I don't get enough sleep overall"],scoring:[{min:0,max:9,level:"Good Sleep",color:"text-green-600",advice:"Your sleep quality appears good. Continue maintaining healthy sleep habits and a consistent schedule."},{min:10,max:19,level:"Mild Issues",color:"text-yellow-600",advice:"You have some sleep quality issues. Try establishing a consistent bedtime routine and limiting screen time before bed."},{min:20,max:29,level:"Moderate Issues",color:"text-orange-600",advice:"Your sleep quality is significantly impacted. Consider implementing sleep hygiene practices and consulting a healthcare provider."},{min:30,max:40,level:"Severe Issues",color:"text-red-600",advice:"Your sleep quality is severely compromised. Please consult a healthcare provider, as chronic sleep issues can significantly impact your mental and physical health."}]}],OL=[{label:"Never",value:0},{label:"Rarely",value:1},{label:"Sometimes",value:2},{label:"Often",value:3},{label:"Always",value:4}];function ML(){return y.jsx("section",{className:"py-20 bg-background",children:y.jsxs("div",{className:"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8",children:[y.jsx("div",{className:"text-center mb-12",children:y.jsxs(He.div,{initial:{opacity:0,y:20},whileInView:{opacity:1,y:0},viewport:{once:!0},children:[y.jsx("div",{className:"inline-block px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4",children:"Free Screenings"}),y.jsx("h2",{className:"font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4",children:"What would you like 